|quote=  In Weyl's wonderful and terrible<sup>1</sup> book ''The Classical Groups'' [W] one may discern two main themes: first, the study of the polynomial invariants for an arbitrary number of (contravariant or covariant) variables for a standard classical group action; second, the isotypic decomposition of the full tensor algebra for such an action.

