This page is a glossary of terms  in [[invariant theory]]. 
For descriptions of particular invariant rings, see [[invariants of a binary form]], [[symmetric polynomials]]. 
For geometric terms used in invariant theory see the [[glossary of classical algebraic geometry]]. 
Definitions of many terms used in invariant theory can be found in {{harv|Sylvester|1853}}, {{harv|Cayley|1860}}, {{harv|Burnside|Panton|1881}}, {{harv|Salmon|1885}}, {{harv|Elliot|1895}}, {{harv|Grace|Young|1903}}, {{harv|Glenn|1915}},   {{harv|Dolgachev|2012}}, and the index to the fourth volume of Sylvester's collected works includes many of the terms invented by him.

