{{term|intermutant}}
{{defn|A special  form of permutant. {{harv|Cayley|1860}} }}

{{term|invariant}}
{{defn|no=1|(Adjective) Fixed by the action of a group}}
{{defn|no=2|(Noun) An absolute invariant, meaning something fixed by a group action.}}
{{defn|no=3|(Noun) A relative invariant, meaning something transforming according to a character of a group. In classical invariant theory it often refers to relatively invariant polynomials in the coefficients of a quantic, considered as a representation of a general linear group.}}

