In [[mathematics]], the '''Hilbert–Mumford criterion''', introduced by [[David Hilbert]] and [[David Mumford]],  characterizes the [[semistable point|semistable]] and stable points of a [[Group action (mathematics)|group action]] on a [[vector space]] in terms of [[eigenvalues and eigenvectors|eigenvalues]] of 1-parameter [[subgroups]] {{harvs|last=Dieudonné|last2=Carrell|year1=1970|year2=1971|loc2=p.58}}.

